title: :indeterminate
description: The `:indeterminate` CSS pseudo-class applies to form elements, such as checkboxes, that are neither checked nor unchecked, but in an indeterminate state.
content: The pseudo-class that applies to form elements, like checkboxes, when they are in an indeterminate state. This means the element is neither checked nor unchecked, often used to indicate a mixed state or partial selection.
